    "feature_label": "BACH2",
    "feature_name": "BACH2",
    "feature_id": null,
    "source_type": "text",
    "source_rationale": "We also identified very small clusters of CD4 and CD8 T cells (20a and 20b, with 18 and 8 cells, respectively) that differed from the major CD4 and CD8 T cell clusters (7 and 6, respectively) by expressing higher levels of genes associated with naïve and/or central memory T cell states (e.g. BACH2, SELL, LEF1) and lower levels of genes encoding cytoskeletal and adhesion molecules (e.g. LGALS1, S100A4, VIM) that were previously found to characterize lung-localized human T cells (47).",
    "source_id": "manuscript.md",
